-----------------------------------
Input description:
----------------------------------
-gobal   rhol/=0 print rholalblx(r) in fort.51   !! attention!! the file will be very huge
         rl/=0       print  rlalblx(r) in fort.52 
         integration=0 Gauss-Legendre quadrature way to do the calculation
         integration=1 Simpson rule to do the calculation
         xsection  ! xsection>0 ,print fort.15, xsection>1, print fort.16
         nnu : number of Gauss points. better nnu>48 
         dwba>0 : use dwba method
                  daba=1  zero-range,solved with Green's function
                  dwba=2  zero-range,solved inhomogeneous equation
                  dwba=3  zero-range,solved with Green's function with finite range correction
                  dwba=4  zero-range,solved inhomogeneous equation with finite range correction
                  dwba=5  finite-range,solved with Green's function
                  dwba=6  finite-range,solved inhomogeneous equation
         accuracy : accuracy of the kernel transformation 
-system  neb: number of E_b^{lab} in outgoing channels     <32 ?      
 
-outgoing 
cc two ways to define the outgoing channels, define each channel or define
    the energy range of outgoing channels
          ecmb: relative energy of channel b in the center of mass frame
          bin=0: without b-bins, just use one energy point
          bin>0: use b-bins method, nnu is the number of Gauss points to do the integration
          wbin: width of b-bin in the momentum space,kmax=k+wbin/2, kmin=k-wbin/2   
          kn: index    
          ecmbmin : minimum energy value of outgoing particle b in c.m.
          ecmbmax : maximum energy value of outgoing particle b in c.m.
          ecmbh   : energy step 
-potential kp1 :index  'a','b','x','p'        
           kp2 : index  corresponds to 'kn' 
           ptype : potential type      ptype=1 woods-saxon
                                       ptype=2 Gaussian    
                                       ptype=3 Koning-Delaroche potentials only for neutron
                                       ptype=4 CH89 only for neutron
                                       ptype=5 Bechetti-Greenless for neutron
                                       ptype=6 yyq06 Phys Rev C 74 044615 
-overlap  kbpot1 : index  'a','b','x','p'  
          kbpot2 : index  corresponds to 'kn'
          lbx : angular momentum between 'b' and 'x'
          sn : spin of 'b'
          jbx :  (l,sn)jbx
          be : bounding energy 
          nfl>0 read the wfs from the file fort.nfl;  nfl=0 do the calculation 
          rbxmax : maximum value of rbx in the integral 
          nbx : gauss quadrature points in the integral with rbx
--------
output
--------
fort.3   : local copy of input 
fort.7   : elastic S-matrix elements
fort.15  : partial cross sections
fort.41  : radial part of scattering wave of channel a
fort.42  : radial part of scattering wave of channel b
fort.43  : regular solution of Gx
fort.44  : irregular solution of Gx 
fort.51 : rholalblx(r)
fort.52 : rlalblx(r)
